<br>
Our necromancer brethren are amazing to duo with.  Just like Wizards are awesome to duo with if you use the right tactics.  <br>
<br>
Necros are ungodly powerful in the hands of a skilled player.  Too bad there aren't too many of those around though.  We might actually see more necromancers around!  Their dots are second to none.  Their pets are almost as good as hours, and when @#%$ starts to hit the fan, they can get out of the hole much more easily than we do.<br>
<br>
/bows to the Necromancers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ylaine76>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1163<br> <font color=#333333>(11/28/02 9:31:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7992.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hehe...</span><hr size=1> I always like good grouping necros, but a lot of soloers have the &quot;I dont know how to group well&quot; syndrome which might lead to bad views of necros... <br>
<br>
One thing I'd like to point out is that necro healing is no longer an advantage heh, in PoP you might as well use bandages with how fast the mobs do damage.  Necros have good dots, the average fight lasts what 45 seconds now? So they can atleast 1 full length dot on there, if not 2.. Which is a decent amount of damage.  Neurotoxin I assume was put in the game to help necros solve the problem of no quick damage, it has an absolutely horrible ratio but it does give them some nuking ability<br>
<br>
All in all I like necros and dont see a point in trying to figure out which one is better.  I am rather dissapointed with the unoriginality of the 61+ pets tho, not to say other classes shouldnt have good pets I just would of rather had *different* pets rather than every class having a level 60 pet which does virtually the same melee damage...<br>
<br>
Mages give up a lot of versatility to be the absolute best class at taking on a mob head to head... blow for blow Mages can take the most damage in direct melee combat without any other class assistance, I find that pretty cool <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  There is no other class (besides beastlords I guess? But havent seen them solo tough mobs) who can go up against a non-slowed 495 hitting mob and win, in melee.. Other classes can kite but our pets have the muscle to survive for 10 seconds (thats so awesome) however we can heal and then alternate rains in between heals, mix in a mend companion and we can kill PoV mobs <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/YlaineEQ/fullsize/cheersig2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
